  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Give Nkoranza Hope Livestock Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HIV/AIDS is spreading at an alarming rate in Ghana, with conservative estimates indicating more than 200 people are infected daily. Formed in August 2000 and operating under the umbrella of St. Theresa&#x2019;s Hospital in Nkoranza, brings together HIV-positive people, as well as AIDS orphans, to help them overcome the stigma associated with the disease and live positively. This project will assist 50 people living with HIV/AIDS and caregivers in Ghana&#x2019;s Nkoranza District by providing income-generating avenues through the distribution of 125 beehives with honey-harvesting equipment, 105 pigs (including 10 breeding boars) and 1000 chickens. Targeted communities will also receive training in animal production and beekeeping, as well as HIV/AIDS education and gender equity training. Over three years, an additional 50 families will also benefit through &#x201C;passing on the gift.&quot;</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">People Living with HIV/AIDS (PLWHA), Farmer households, Women, Youth</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Theoretical and hands-on training in beekeeping, small ruminant management and poultry production. Training in project management and record keeping. Training in compost preparation. Training on leadership skills development.  Training on the 12 HPI cornerstones. Training on gender equity. HIV/AIDS awareness creation. Farmer to farmer visitation.</narrative>
  </description>
